Title: 
 Value Segmentation: A Model for the Measurement of Values and Value Systems.

Journal: Journal of Consumer Research
Pages: 208-18
Issue: 2
Volume: 18
Year: 1991
Month:  September 
Abstract:

 This article develops a model for the measurement of human values that,
 rather than obtain aggregate measurements, identifies distinct value
 systems within a population and classifies individuals according to them.
 These value systems are inferred from the stated priority rankings,
 obtained from each individual via the Rokeach value survey.


