Author-Name:   Kolbe, Richard H
Author-Name:  Burnett, Melissa S
Title: 
 Content-Analysis Research: An Examination of Applications with Directives for Improving Research Reliability and Objectivity.

Journal: Journal of Consumer Research
Pages: 243-50
Issue: 2
Volume: 18
Year: 1991
Month:  September 
Abstract:

 This article provides an empirical review and synthesis of published
 studies that have used content-analysis methods. Harold Kassarjian's
 critical guidelines for content-analysis research were used to examine the
 methods employed in 128 studies. The guidelines were expanded by providing
 an empirical investigation of multiple dimensions of objectivity.
 Reliability issues were also assessed by examining factors central to the
 replication and interjudge coefficient calculations. The findings indicate
 a general need for improvement in the application of content-analysis
 methods. Suggestions for calculating reliability coefficients and for
 improving the objectivity and reliability of research are offered.


