Author-Name:   Armstrong, J Scott
Title: 
 Prediction of Consumer Behavior by Experts and Novices.

Journal: Journal of Consumer Research
Pages: 251-56
Issue: 2
Volume: 18
Year: 1991
Month:  September 
Abstract:

 Are those who are familiar with scientific research on consumer behavior
 better able to make predictions about phenomena in this field? Predictions
 were made for 105 hypotheses from 20 empirical studies selected from
 "Journal of Consumer Research." A total of 1,736 predictions were obtained
 from 16 academics, 12 practitioners, and 43 high school students. The
 practitioners were correct on 58.2 percent of the hypotheses, the students
 on 56.6 percent, and the academics on 51.3 percent. No group performed
 better than chance.


